Class KozaCrossover

java.lang.Object

All Implemented Interfaces:
GPCrossover, ConfigListener, Listener, Crossover, Operator
public class KozaCrossover
extends SubtreeCrossover

This class implements a Koza style crossover operation on two CandidatePrograms.

Koza crossover performs a one point exchange with the choice of a swap point being either a function or terminal node with assigned probabilities. This class provides a constructor for specifying a probability of selecting a function swap point. The default constructor uses the typical rates of 90% function node swap point and 10% terminal node swap points.

If a model is provided then the following parameters are loaded upon every configure event:

  • random number generator

If the getModel method returns null then no model is set and whatever static parameters have been set as parameters to the constructor or using the standard accessor methods will be used. If any compulsory parameters remain unset when the crossover is performed then an IllegalStateException will be thrown.

See Also:
SubtreeCrossover, OnePointCrossover
